# Memory Bank is Authoritative

- Always read Memory Bank files before starting any task:
  - [memory-bank/projectbrief.md](mdc:memory-bank/projectbrief.md)
  - [memory-bank/productContext.md](mdc:memory-bank/productContext.md)
  - [memory-bank/activeContext.md](mdc:memory-bank/activeContext.md)
  - [memory-bank/systemPatterns.md](mdc:memory-bank/systemPatterns.md)
  - [memory-bank/techContext.md](mdc:memory-bank/techContext.md)
  - [memory-bank/progress.md](mdc:memory-bank/progress.md)

- After meaningful changes:
  - Update `activeContext.md` with current focus, recent changes, next steps
  - Reflect new/changed endpoints in `systemPatterns.md`
  - Capture tech/config/schema changes in `techContext.md`
  - Record status updates and known issues in `progress.md`

- Prefer clear, verbose naming in code edits; avoid cryptic abbreviations.
- Keep edits small and incremental with clear commit messages.